description:
FieldReplaceableUnit: Table describing the attributes of field replaceable units in a radio access network.

- dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the unit is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
- CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
- Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
- Id3:  Internal identifier for the field replaceable unit.
- vsDataType: Data type identifier.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.hwTestResult: Hardware test result.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.userLabel: User-defined label.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.positionRef: Reference to the unit's position within the network infrastructure.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.positionInformation: Position information.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.floorInformation: Floor information of the unit's location.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.administrativeState: Administrative state of the unit (e.g., LOCKED, UNLOCKED).
- FieldReplaceableUnit.positionCoordinates: Coordinates of the unit's position.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.supportUnitRef: Reference to the supporting unit.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.fieldReplaceableUnitId: Unique identifier of the field replaceable unit.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.productData: Product data associated with the unit.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.isSharedWithExternalMe: Indicates whether the unit is shared with an external management entity.
- FieldReplaceableUnit.operationalState: Operational state of the unit (e.g., ENABLED, DISABLED).
